# [V6OPS](../wg/v6ops.html)

## Summary

The V6OPS working group session at IETF 125 focused on the progression of several key operational documents. Major topics included the relaxation of restrictions on Well-Known Prefixes (WKP) for NAT64 when dealing with private address space, and the updates to stateful NAT64 specifications. The chairs reported significant progress on multiple working group items, including the advancement of several documents to the RFC Editor queue and the publication of new RFCs.

